# Markdown documentation language (English only)

## Rule

- **All `*.md` files** in this repository (including `README.md`, design notes, `docs/**`, ADRs, and user manuals under version control) must use **English** for:
  - Titles, headings, and body prose
  - Table cell text and list items
  - Diagram captions and labels where you author the text (Mermaid node labels, descriptions)
- **Exceptions:**
  - **Quoted third-party text**, legal notices, or verbatim excerpts copied from external specs (keep original language in quotes when required).
  - **User-facing UI strings** reproduced inside docs for reference (e.g. button labels in screenshots descriptions may stay as in-product).
  - A file explicitly requested **by the user** to be in another language for a named deliverable (localized manual export, etc.) — then follow that one-off request for that file only.
  - **Identifiers** (`sensor.cfg.get`, file paths, protocol constants) remain as-is.

## Agent behavior

- When **creating or editing** Markdown documentation in `t3d-extension`, write and maintain it in **English**.
- If an existing `*.md` file mixes another language into prose, **translate the prose to English** when editing that file, unless the user asked to keep a specific section.
- This rule applies to **repository artifacts**, not to chat replies (see `communication-language.mdc` for conversational language with the user).

## Rationale

Keep technical documentation consistent for the team, search, diffs, and tooling; avoid mixed-language design docs and READMEs in the same tree.

## Relationship to other rules

- **Conversational replies** to the user may still be **Thai and/or English** per `communication-language.mdc`.
- **Repository Markdown** is **English only** per this rule.
